```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "resource_requirements": {
      "gpu": 1
    },
    "environment_setup": {
      "virtualenv": "/vol/bitbucket/${USER}/myvenv",
      "cuda": "/vol/cuda/11.0.3-cudnn8.0.5.39"
    },
    "libraries": {
      "pytorch": "torch torchvision"
    },
    "tools": {
      "nvidia-smi": "/usr/bin/nvidia-smi"
    }
  }
}
```

This script is using **Slurm** for job scheduling and resource management. It requests one GPU and sets up a virtual environment with a specific CUDA version. It installs PyTorch and runs nvidia-smi to check the GPU status. It also includes some basic system information gathering with `uptime`.
